(CHAPTER 1 — GUIDANCE COMPUTER SUBSYSTEM) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1.1 COMPONENT OVERVIEW) Tj T*
(The MK-4 guidance computer \(P/N GC-4521-A\) is the primary navigation) Tj T*
(processor for the Patriot PAC-3 interceptor missile system. It integrates) Tj T*
(inertial measurement data with terminal seeker inputs to compute intercept) Tj T*
(geometry in real time.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Compliance: MIL-STD-1553B \(data bus\), MIL-DTL-38999 \(connectors\).) Tj T*
(CAGE Code: 12345) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1.2 SUBSYSTEM COMPONENTS) Tj T*
(The guidance subsystem contains the following assemblies:) Tj T*
( - Inertial Measurement Unit \(P/N IMU-7700\): accelerometers and gyroscopes) Tj T*
( - Terminal Seeker Assembly \(P/N TSA-2201\): radar seeker head) Tj T*
( - Power Conditioning Unit \(P/N PCU-0510\): 28VDC regulated supply) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(The IMU-7700 is a subsystem of the MK-4 guidance computer.) Tj T*
(The PCU-0510 provides power to the IMU-7700.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1.3 SPECIFICATIONS) Tj T*
( - Operating temperature range: -40°C to +85°C) Tj T*
( - Input voltage: 28 VDC ± 2V) Tj T*
( - Processing speed: 1000 MHz) Tj T*
( - Memory: 256 MB SDRAM) Tj T*
( - MTBF: 5000 hours) Tj T*
( - Weight: 2.3 kg) Tj T*
( - Dimensions: 200 mm × 150 mm × 75 mm) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1.4 APPLICABLE STANDARDS) Tj T*
(This subsystem meets the requirements of:) Tj T*
( - MIL-STD-461G \(electromagnetic interference\)) Tj T*
( - MIL-STD-810H \(environmental engineering\)) Tj T*
( - MIL-PRF-38535 \(integrated circuits\)) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(1.5 KNOWN FAILURE MODES) Tj T*
( - Crystal oscillator drift above +70°C operating temperature) Tj T*
( - Connector corrosion on TSA-2201 in salt-fog environments) Tj T*
() Tj T*
ET
